                                                                                                                                                                                                     3 records fall
                      
	Manchester: Olympic gold medallist Kirsty Coventry led the way as three world records tumbled at of the world short-course swimming championships on Wednesday. Coventry broke the womens 400m medley short-course mark that had stood for six years and the US men and Dutch women shattered relay records.         
	Zimbabwes Coventry, Olympic 200m backstroke champion, clocked 4:26.52 seconds to beat the 4:27.83 set by Yana Klochkova of Ukraine in Paris on January 19, 2002.         
	The US swam home in the mens 100 freestyle relay in 3:08.44 to beat the 3:09.57 mark set by Sweden at the world short-course championships in Athens on March 16, 2000.         
	The Dutch womens 4x200 team of Inge Dekker, Femke Heemskerk, Marleen Veldhuis and Ranomi Kromowidjojo clocked 7:38.90 to annihilate the 7:46.30 set by Russia at the world short-course meet in Moscow on April 3, 2002.           (REUTERS)                                                                                                                      
